                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18420822-2553-offence-1 t18420822-name-1881"></join>Samuel Jones</persName>, his master; and that he had been before convicted of felony.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420822-name-1882" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1882" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1882" type="surname" value="JONES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1882" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>SAMUEL JONES</persName>
                  </hi>. I deal in coals, and live in Neptune-street, New<lb></lb>ington—on the 4th of August I employed the prisoner, who said he was in distress, to take out some herrings to sell—I gave him a barrow with 300 herrings to sell—he was to account for them—I gave him sixpence the night before to get victuals with, as he said he was in distress, and I gave him another sixpence when he went away with the barrow and herrings—he never brought them or the money back—I saw nothing more of him until he was in custody on the 13th—on the 19th, since he was committed, the barrow has been left at my house.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184208220271"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. You agreed to lend me the money and was to go partners with me; I was to go and sell the things. <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. I employed you, and was to pay you for your day's work when you returned.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420822-name-1883" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1883" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1883" type="surname" value="BROOK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1883" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES BROOK</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman—I took the prisoner in charge on Saturday the 13th—I told him the charge—he said he sent the barrow home by a boy they called "<hi rend="italic">Fishey,"</hi> that he sold the herrings for 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—he said the boy's father worked at the gas-woks—I inquired there, and found the boy is about eight years old.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence</hi>. I returned the barrow on Monday evening by a boy who is eighteen years of age; he could not find the house out—I was remanded when I was taken, but could not find him—my brother has since found him and returned the barrow to Mr. Jones.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420822-name-1884" type="witnessName">
